summary: This is a calendar entry for the administration of juror questionnaires in the Ghislaine Maxwell case, scheduled for November 12-13, 2021, at the Foley Square Courthouse. It lists the event organizer and various attendees, primarily from law enforcement and the U.S. Attorney's Office.

events.title: Maxwell Juror Questionnaire Administration Start
events.description: Scheduled start date for administering juror questionnaires in the Ghislaine Maxwell trial.

events.title: Maxwell Juror Questionnaire Administration End
events.description: Scheduled end date for administering juror questionnaires in the Ghislaine Maxwell trial.

keyFacts: The juror questionnaire process for Ghislaine Maxwell's trial was scheduled for November 12-13, 2021.
The event was organized by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).
Attendees included representatives from the FBI, NYPD, USANYS, and contractors.
The calendar entry was created on August 27, 2021, and last modified on November 11, 2021.
The event was held at the Foley Square Courthouse in New York.
